HEADWORD: Cheiloplasty
<hw>Chei"lo*plas`ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a lip
+ <ets>-plasty</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>The process of
forming an artificial tip or part of a lip, by using for the purpose a
piece of healthy tissue taken from some neighboring part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

